    "answer_id" : 60734235,
    "question_id" : 12721076,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>We'll check a Collection object is empty, null or not. these all methods which are given below, are present in org.apache.commons.collections4.CollectionUtils package.</p>\n\n<p>Check on List or set type of collection Objects.</p>\n\n<pre><code>CollectionUtils.isEmpty(listObject);\nCollectionUtils.isNotEmpty(listObject);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Check on Map type of Objects.</p>\n\n<pre><code>MapUtils.isEmpty(mapObject);\nMapUtils.isNotEmpty(mapObject);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The return type of all methods is boolean.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 12368549,
      "reputation" : 400,
      "user_id" : 9019654,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/MFxsY.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Kevin KOUOMEU",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/9019654/kevin-kouomeu"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1691065551,
    "creation_date" : 1691065551,
    "answer_id" : 76828052,
    "question_id" : 12721076,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Taking the case you collection is a List, you can simply use this</p>\n<pre><code>private boolean collectionIsNotNullAndNotEmpty(List&lt;?&gt; collection) {\n    return Objects.nonNull(collection) &amp;&amp; !collection.isEmpty();\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
